## kubectl get pods


kubectl logs <pod-name>


Specify a Container (if multiple containers in a pod):

If a pod has multiple containers, you can specify which container's logs you want to retrieve by adding the -c or --container flag followed by the container name:

bash
Copy code
kubectl logs <pod-name> -c <container-name>

kubectl logs my-pod

Or, if the pod has multiple containers:

kubectl logs my-pod -c my-container
